  3 /** Painter
  4 
  5 	Painter interact with the canvases and the html page. It binds
  6 	to / uses several layer of overlapping canvas elements. Think
  7 	of it a bit like the view part of a MVC model.
  8 
  9 	<pre>
 10 	>                       +---------------------+
 11 	>                       V                     |
 12 	>    Canvas/html <-- Painter <-- Frame <-- Diagram
 13 	>           |       ^^^^^^^^                ^
 14 	>           |                               |
 15 	>           +-------------------------------+
 16 	</pre>
 17 
 18 	@class
 19 	@param {string} CanvasIDString The ID of the canvas element
 20 	@param {number} CanvasHeight The height of the canvas element
 21 	@param {number} CanvasWidth The width of the canvas element
 22 	@param {blockSize} blockSize The size of the canvas element
 23 	@requires Frame
 24 	@requires Diagram
 25 
 26 */
 27 function Painter(CanvasIDString) {
 28 	/*
 29 		Default canvas size (same as fumen) :
 30 		- height: 193px
 31 		- width: 80px
 32 		- block size: 8*8px
 33 	*/
 34 
 35 	/** A variable referencing the class, used to exploit closure stuff in other methods*/
 36 	var myself = this;
 37 
 38 	// Default parameter method could be taken from: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/894860/how-do-i-make-a-default-value-for-a-parameter-to-a-javascript-function

 41 	this.CanvasHeight = 177;
 42 	/** Width of the Canvas in px.*/
 43 	this.CanvasWidth = 97;
 44 	/**Size of a block element in px.*/
 45 	this.blockSize = 8;
 46 
 47 	this.IDString = CanvasIDString;

 60 	/** Get the 2d context of the related canvas*/

 79 	this.CanvasBackground = $('#' + CanvasIDString + '-background');

162 	/** Erase the content one layer (the canvas still exists)..
163 
164 		@param {string} layer Define which layer will be erased. Possible value: 'inactive', 'active','preview', 'nexthold', 'whiteborder' or 'all'
165 	*/
166 	this.eraseLayer = function (layer) {
167 		var Canvas;
168 		switch (layer)
169 		{
170 			case 'decoration':
171 				Context = this.ContextDeco;
172 				break;
173 			case 'inactive':
174 				Context = this.ContextPF;
175 				break;
176 			case 'preview':
177 				Context = this.ContextPreview;
178 				break;
179 			case 'active':
180 				Context = this.ContextActive;
181 				break;
182 			case 'nexthold':
183 				Context = this.ContextNextHold;
184 				break;
185 			case 'whiteborder':
186 				Context = this.ContextWhiteborder;
187 				break;
188 			case 'all':
189 				Context = this.ContextPF;
190 				
191 				this.ContextDeco.clearRect(0,0,this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight);
192 				this.ContextPreview.clearRect(0,0,this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight);
193 				this.ContextActive.clearRect(0,0,this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight);
194 				this.ContextNextHold.clearRect(0,0,this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight);
195 				this.ContextWhiteborder.clearRect(0,0,this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight);
196 				break;
197 		}
198 		Context.clearRect(0,0,this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight);
199 	};

201 	/** Erase a 'block' area at the designated coordinate.

203 		@param {number} x x position, in block unit

245 	/** Draw the progressbar according to its status given in parameter
246 
247 		@param {number} CurrentFrame Which frame are we on ?
248 		@param {number} TotalFrame How many frame there are
249 	*/
250 	this.drawProgressbar = function(CurrentFrame,TotalFrame){
251 		if(CurrentFrame <= TotalFrame && CurrentFrame > 0) // filter out invalid input
252 		{
253 			this.ContextProgressbar.clearRect(0,0,this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight);
254 			this.ContextProgressbar.beginPath();
255 			this.ContextProgressbar.rect(0,0,parseInt((CurrentFrame/TotalFrame)*100,10),24);
256 			this.ContextProgressbar.fillStyle= 'gray';
257 			this.ContextProgressbar.fill();
258 			this.ContextProgressbar.closePath();
259 		}
260 	};

262 	/** Draw a TGM-like white pixel around inactive blocks in the whole playfield.
263 
264 		@param playfield The playfield on which to draw the white border
265 	*/
266 	this.drawWhiteBorder = function(playfield)
267 	{
268 		// todo: do an 'anti white pixel' that clear instead of draw
269 		// we iterate on the playfield, look in each case if there's something in it, then look at the neighbour for empty cases to paint some borders in these cases
270 		this.eraseLayer('whiteborder');
271 		//this.ContextWhiteborder.rect((this.PFOriginX+i*this.blockSize)-1,this.PFOriginY+j*this.blockSize-1,1,this.blockSize+1);
272 		for(var i = 0, istop = playfield.length; i < istop; i++) { // for optimisation: caching the length instead of calculating it each time
273 			for(var j = 0, jstop = playfield[0].length; j < jstop; j++) {
274 				if (playfield[i][j][0]) {
275 					this.drawLocalWhiteBorder(playfield,i,j);
276 				}
277 			}
278 		}
279 	};

287 		// Todo (procrastination level: 99999): I cannot get really good squary corners...

506 	/** Draw a block sized grid on the background layer, for no particular reason
507 	*/
508 	this.drawGrid = function(){
509 		// todo: change if width/height variable
510 		this.ContextBackground.beginPath();
511 
512 		// Rectangle method
513 		// using line (ctx.moveTo, lineTo, stroke()) doesn't give good results
514 		this.ContextBackground.beginPath();
515 		//hor
516 		for(var i = 1; i <= 9; i++) {
517 			this.ContextBackground.rect(this.PFOriginX+((i)*this.blockSize),this.PFOriginY,1,20*this.blockSize);
518 		}
519 		//vert
520 		for(var i = 1; i <= 19; i++) {
521 			this.ContextBackground.rect(this.PFOriginX,this.PFOriginY+((i)*this.blockSize),10*this.blockSize,1);
522 		}
523 		this.ContextBackground.fillStyle = '#444';
524 		this.ContextBackground.fill();
525 
526 		this.ContextBackground.closePath();
527 	};

529 	/** Draws the Tetrion (the playfield's border).
530 
531 		@param {string} kind Define what kind of tetrion you want. Currently supported:
532 		'master' (gray-bluish), 'easy' (green) and 'death' (red). Defaults to master if
533 		none is selected
534 	*/
535 	
536 	
537 	this.drawBorder = function(kind){
538 		var color1 = '#afafaf';
539 		var color2 = '#46545f';
540 
541 		switch(kind)
542 		{
543 			case 'master':
544 				color1 = '#afafaf';
545 				color2 = '#46545f';
546 			break;
547 
548 			case 'easy':
549 				color1 = '#afafaf';
550 				color2 = '#475f46';
551 			break;
552 
553 			case 'death':
554 				color1 = '#ac434a';
555 				color2 = '#5f0004';
556 			break;
557 
558 			default:
559 				color1 = '#afafaf';
560 				color2 = '#46545f';
561 			break;
562 
563 		}
564 
565 		var radgrd1 = this.ContextBorder.createRadialGradient(0,0,this.blockSize,
566 															0,0,this.CanvasWidth-2*this.blockSize),
567 			radgrd2 = this.ContextBorder.createRadialGradient(this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight,this.blockSize,
568 															this.CanvasWidth,this.CanvasHeight,this.CanvasWidth-2*this.blockSize);
569 		radgrd1.addColorStop(0,color1);
570 		radgrd1.addColorStop(1,color2);
571 		radgrd2.addColorStop(0,color1);
572 		radgrd2.addColorStop(1,color2);
573 
574 		var grd_hor = this.ContextBorder.createLinearGradient(0,0,this.CanvasWidth-2*this.blockSize,0), // multiple declaration in a single statement ftw !
575 			grd_hor_rev = this.ContextBorder.createLinearGradient(0,0,this.CanvasWidth-2*this.blockSize,0),
576 
577 			grd_vert = this.ContextBorder.createLinearGradient(0,0,0,this.CanvasWidth-2*this.blockSize),
578 			grd_vert_rev = this.ContextBorder.createLinearGradient(0,0,0,this.CanvasWidth-2*this.blockSize);
579

1863 				output += 'A~'+this.frames[final_frame].activePieceType;

1865 				output += tmp;

1935 								candidate_case[parseFloat(k+1)].push(alphanumconvert(i)+alphanumconvert(j));
1936 								newly_added = true;
1937 							}
1938 
1939 						}
1940 
1941 					}
1942 				}

2716 	/** Load the playfield from a descriptive string.

2721 	this.load = function(str, format){

2723 		{

2725 		}
2726 		/* Example
2727 
2728 		A~Iigh_I~Taababbcagihihjii~Zai~Jde~Sdgefegff_
2729 
2730 		Algorithm
2731 		- make an array out of the 1st level marker '_'
2732 		- make an array out of the 2nd level marker '~'
2733 		- parse the 1st element of the 2nd level
2734 		- compute
2735 		- iterate over all the string
2736 
2737 		properties[0] == A~Icdccw_
2738 			subproperties[0] == A
2739 			subproperties[1] == cdccw
2740 		properties[1] == I~Tadaeafbfbhcdcecfcgch~Gededeeefegehfdfffh~Shdhdhehfhhidifihjdjfjgjh_
2741 			subproperties[0] == I
2742 			subproperties[1] == Tadaeafbfbhcdcecfcgch
2743 			subproperties[2] == Gededeeefegehfdfffh
2744 			subproperties[3] == Shdhdhehfhhidifihjdjfjgjh_
2745 		*/
2746 		if(!str){return;} //check if there's nothing
2747 			var properties = str.split('_');
2748 
2749 		for(var i=0, istop = properties.length; i<istop; i++){
2750 			var subproperties = properties[i].split('~');
2751 				switch(subproperties[0])
2752 				{
2753 				case 'A': // active piece
2754 						if(subproperties[1].charAt(0) !== 'E')
2755 						{
2756 							this.activePieceType = subproperties[1].charAt(0);
2757 							this.activePieceOrientation = subproperties[1].slice(3);
2758 							this.activePiecePositionX = alphanumconvert(subproperties[1].charAt(1));
2759 							this.activePiecePositionY = alphanumconvert(subproperties[1].charAt(2));
2760 						}

3002 	this.addPiece = function(x,y,type,orientation,mode,drop){
3003 		var matrix = getMatrix(type, orientation, this.RS);
3004 		var still_droping = true;

3016 					}
3017 				}
3018 			}
3019 			if (counter != 4) {
3020 				still_droping = false;
3021 			}
3022 			else
3023 			{
3024 				y++;
3025 			}
3026 		}

3038 		}

4369 (function() {
4370     var lastTime = 0;

4372     for(var x = 0, xstop = vendors.length; x < xstop && !window.requestAnimationFrame; ++x) {
4373         window.requestAnimationFrame = window[vendors[x]+'RequestAnimationFrame'];
4374         window.cancelAnimationFrame = window[vendors[x]+'CancelAnimationFrame'] ||
4375                                       window[vendors[x]+'CancelRequestAnimationFrame'];
4376     }
4377 
4378     if (!window.requestAnimationFrame)
4379         {window.requestAnimationFrame = function(callback, element) {
4380             var currTime = new Date().getTime();
4381             var timeToCall = Math.max(0, 16 - (currTime - lastTime));
4382             var id = window.setTimeout(function() { callback(currTime + timeToCall); },
4383               timeToCall);
4384             lastTime = currTime + timeToCall;
4385             return id;
4386         };}

4388     if (!window.cancelAnimationFrame)
4389          {window.cancelAnimationFrame = function(id) {
4390             clearTimeout(id);

4394 // compare prototype courtesy of Patrick Hunlock http://www.hunlock.com/blogs/Mastering_Javascript_Arrays#quickIDX41
4395 Array.prototype.compare = function(testArr) {
4396     if (this.length != testArr.length)
4397 		{return false;}
4398     for(var i = 0, istop = testArr.length; i < istop; i++) {
4399         if (this[i].compare) {
4400             if (!this[i].compare(testArr[i]))
4401 				{return false;}
4402         }
4403         if (this[i] !== testArr[i]) {return false;}
4404     }
4405     return true;
4406 };
